<treatmentCitation id="9C27D232FC003C666E8AFE5DFDC2FE62" author="Casey TL" box="[140,564,483,510]" page="62" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" year="1918">
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC003C666E8AFE5DFDC2FE62" authority="Casey, 1918: 62" authorityName="Casey" authorityPageNumber="62" authorityYear="1918" box="[140,564,483,510]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pernotum">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC003C666E8AFE5DFE83FE62" box="[140,373,483,509]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">Bembidion pernotum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="791789D2FC003C666F7DFE5AFDC2FE62" author="Casey TL" box="[379,564,483,510]" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" pagination="1 - 223" refId="ref6089" refString="Casey TL (1918) A review of the North American Bembidiinae. Memoirs on the Coleoptera 8: 1 - 223." type="journal article" year="1918">Casey, 1918: 62</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
</treatmentCitation>
. Type locality Jemez Springs, 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC003C666D85FE5AFBEEFE62" box="[899,1048,483,510]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
. 
<typeStatus id="C23D4A81FC003C666A24FE5AFEF7FDBE" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">Lectotype</typeStatus>
female, designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="791789D2FC003C666C10FDB9FD4FFDBE" author="Erwin TL" box="[534,697,519,545]" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" pagination="165 - 187" refId="ref6233" refString="Erwin TL (1984) Studies of the tribe Bembidiini (Coleoptera: Carabidae): lectotype designations and species group assignments for Bembidion species described by Thomas L. Casey and others. Pan-Pacific Entomologist 60: 165 - 187." type="journal article" year="1984">Erwin (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, in USNM (type number 36922), examined.
</treatmentCitationGroup>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1D39F423FC003C666E8AFDCEFD73FCA4" blockId="14.[140,1107,624,827]" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">
This species is known from northern 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC003C666C2DFDCFFD4DFD15" box="[555,699,624,651]" country="United States of America" name="New Mexico" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">New Mexico</collectingRegion>
and southern 
<collectingRegion id="DF423AC1FC003C666D5BFDCEFC3DFD15" box="[861,971,624,650]" country="United States of America" name="Colorado" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">Colorado</collectingRegion>
. Individuals are colored similarly to 
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC003C666F94FD2AFDDDFD32" box="[402,555,659,685]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversale">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC003C666F94FD2AFDDDFD32" box="[402,555,659,685]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. transversale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but are brighter and more reddish, and are more convex and shinier than other members of the group, with larger punctures in the elytral striae, and more convex intervals. While their color pattern is similar to members of the 
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC003C666ED2FD40FE99FC88" box="[212,367,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="transversale">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC003C666ED2FD40FE99FC88" box="[212,367,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. transversale</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group, male genitalia and DNA sequences indicate a much closer relationship to 
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC003C666F31FC9FFE23FCA5" box="[311,469,801,826]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mexicanum">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC003C666F31FC9FFE23FCA5" box="[311,469,801,826]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. mexicanum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="DA868FA0FC003C666C0BFC9FFD88FCA5" authorityName="LeConte" authorityYear="1857" box="[525,638,800,826]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Bembidium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lugubre">
<emphasis id="2FF22831FC003C666C0BFC9FFD88FCA5" box="[525,638,800,826]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="29">B. lugubre</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
